summary: Playing With Fire:From Beneath by WiL-Woods “This is another scene from "Playing With Fire", the RP I did with TyrineCarver Saia...
caption:
Playing With Fire:From Beneath by WiL-Woods
“This is another scene from “Playing With Fire”, the RP I did with TyrineCarver

Saia and Darth Sinistar are embarked on a mission across Yavin IV when they suddenly lose touch with the Force. They are attacked from underground by a genetically enhanced Massassi Sith mutant. The creature was created by Exar Kun, and was implanted with a ysallimari (or however you spell it) which negated their ability to use the Force.
*I just completely nerded out, didn’t I?*

This particular piece was pretty tedious. I did it as a panorama and it measures in at 22" X 34".

Darth Sinistar was created by yours truly,
Saia created by TyrineCarver“



Please visit the artist’s DeviantArt pages

summary: Uuuggh @ the official Star Wars FB calling Steve Yedlin “master” for a couple of pretty shots in TLJ. Any first-year film...
body:
Uuuggh @ the official Star Wars FB calling Steve Yedlin “master” for a couple of pretty shots in TLJ. Any first-year film student can do some pretty wide shots, that’s not the difficult part of cinematography at all. 

The rest of it lacked intuition, dynamics, creativity or any kind of effort when it comes to blocking and visual direction.

The only Star Wars DP that deserves to be called “master” is Greig Fraser.

(Guess we’re back to the “Rian Johnson and his team are unparalleled geniuses” propaganda, then. *sigh*)
